id: pm-pkdpyz
title: Compatibility gate rejects compact legacy create envelopes after release promotion
description: "Update previous-version compatibility fixture seeding to accept the canonical compact create response id as well as legacy full item.id, so publishing lean mutation output cannot make the next main CI run fail."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[5]: "area:ci","area:release",compatibility,regression,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-21T16:06:13.316Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T16:09:10.545Z"
author: codex-tracker-governance
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "Fixture ID extraction accepts top-level id and item.id while rejecting malformed envelopes; regression tests cover compact, full, and malformed task and issue create responses; node scripts/release/compatibility-check.mjs --base-version 2026.7.21 --json passes in a clean temporary project; the exact-head Gates (compat) GitHub check is green"
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: high
confidence: high
reporter: codex-tracker-governance
severity: high
environment: GitHub Actions Gates (compat) and local compatibility-check against @unbrained/pm-cli@2026.7.21
repro_steps: Run node scripts/release/compatibility-check.mjs --base-version 2026.7.21 --json from current main; observe Legacy create did not return a valid task id.
expected_result: "Compatibility seeding accepts both canonical compact {id,status,changed_field_count} and legacy full {item:{id}} create envelopes, then completes migration validation."
actual_result: "seedLegacyData reads only taskCreate.item.id and issueCreate.item.id; the published compact envelope supplies top-level id, so the gate exits before migration validation."
affected_version: 2026.7.21
component: scripts/release/compatibility-check.mjs
regression: true
customer_impact: Blocks the main compatibility gate and weakens release confidence immediately after compact mutation output promotion.
